1.2
log
@Where a program with an rc script _requires_ a certain command line
parameter to daemonize, move the parameter from daemon to daemon_flags,
so that the user cannot inadvertently prevent it from daemonizing by
adjusting the flags.

Discussed with ajacoutot and schwarze, this method was suggested
by schwarze@@ as a simpler alternative to my diff. ok aja@@
@
text
@#!/bin/sh
#
# $OpenBSD: pdnsd.rc,v 1.1 2011/10/14 07:00:51 ajacoutot Exp $

daemon="${TRUEPREFIX}/sbin/pdnsd -d"

. /etc/rc.d/rc.subr

rc_reload() {
	${TRUEPREFIX}/sbin/pdnsd-ctl config
}

rc_cmd $1
@


1.1
log
@Add an rc script, from frantisek holop.
Tweak the port a bit while here.
@
text
@d3 1
a3 1
# $OpenBSD$
d5 1
a5 2
daemon="${TRUEPREFIX}/sbin/pdnsd"
daemon_flags="-d"
@

